                <note rend="inline" type="source">393.1111 Nelson, Bert N./2: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-10-16T12:00:00+08:00"
                            >October 16, 1930—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received October 16—5:55
                        a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>907. Hankow’s October 14, 5 p.m. The Legation is telegraphing Adams to take this
                    matter up at once with the Ministry of Foreign Affairs with a view to effecting
                    the release of the Reverend Nelson at the earliest possible moment.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
